CARLSBAD, Calif. (AP) _ Arlo Technologies Inc. (ARLO) on Tuesday reported a loss of $8.5 million in its first quarter.The Carlsbad, California-based company said it had a loss of 10 cents per share. Earnings, adjusted for stock option expense and non-recurring costs, came to 1 cent per share.The results surpassed Wall Street expectations. The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for a loss of 3 cents per share.The maker of smart connected devices posted revenue of $124.8 million in the period, also exceeding Street forecasts. Three analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $114.9 million.For the current quarter ending in July, Arlo Technologies expects its results to range from a loss of 8 cents per share to a loss of 3 cents per share.The company said it expects revenue in the range of $105 million to $115 million for the fiscal second quarter.Arlo Technologies shares have decreased 37% since the beginning of the year. In the final minutes of trading on Tuesday, shares hit $6.61, an increase of slightly more than 9% in the last 12 months.ADVERTISEMENT_____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on ARLO at https://www.zacks.com/ap/ARLO